Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.58,0:01:53.67,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:112587,113671}Wow, what a delight!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:58.13,Default,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:113671,118134}{\fad(0,500)}— Episode 18 —\NThe Song Of The Port{NOTE:第18話\\N港にこだまする歌}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.42,0:02:02.76,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:119427,122764}I've never seen shells as big as these.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:04.70,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:122764,124708}Thank you, Nozomi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:09.19,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:125984,129195}I caught them with\Na group of divers I met.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.86,0:02:14.70,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:129863,134701}You're kidding! How did you learn to dive\Nso well? Tell me everything, Nozomi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.45,0:02:18.20,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:135452,138204}Well, at first it was a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.08,0:02:23.71,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:139080,143710}But by the end of our trip, I was told that\NI could become a professional diver if I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:26.71,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:144085,146713}No way! For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.71,0:02:29.09,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:146713,149090}But what was Mr. Egawa thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.09,0:02:33.17,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:149090,153178}Why would he want you to join the divers?\NSometimes I just don't understand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.13,0:02:37.84,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:155138,157849}Maybe he's getting senile…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:40.31,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:157849,160310}Who is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.64,0:02:42.22,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:160643,162228}Ah, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:44.39,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:162228,164397}Ah, I meant…\Nthe mailman!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:46.31,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:164397,166316}Welcome home, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:49.73,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:166983,169736}I was just going to your office\Nto express my thanks for our trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:57.86,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:173656,177869}Nozomi, follow me to\Nthe study room for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:02:59.03,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:177869,179037}Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:05.04,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:182874,185043}Study room?\NDoes that mean?…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:07.92,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:186961,187921}Nozomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:09.21,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:187921,189214}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.21,0:03:11.80,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:189214,191800}I want you to sing something to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.80,0:03:12.88,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:191800,192884}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:15.38,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:192884,195386}Let's see…\NWhich one would be good…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:17.01,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:195386,197013}There. Try singing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.72,0:03:20.55,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:198723,200558}{\i1}"The Wounded Bird"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:22.39,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:200558,202393}{\i1}This is Miki-san's song…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.40,0:03:34.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:209400,214072}{\i1}Why does he want me\Nto sing this one in particular?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.28,0:03:40.37,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:218284,220370}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.37,0:03:41.07,Default,Mine Nozomi,0,0,0,,{TIME:220370,221079}Right.
